{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπι-λάμπω</b>, <br /> <b>shine after</b> or <b>thereupon</b>, ἠέλιος δ᾽ ἐπέλαμψε <b>thereupon</b> the sun <b>shone forth</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Il. 17.650 \">Refs</a>]; of the moon, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hymnus ad Mamercus Elegiacus” 141, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.044d, etc.; ὥς σφι ἡμέρη ἐπέλαμψε 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.14, compare 3.135 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡμέρης ἐπιλαμψάσης when day <b>had fully come</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 7.13; also ἔαρος ἐπιλάμψαντος [prev. author] 8.130. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3>. <b>shine upon</b> (a place), <i>absolutely</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 6, X. “Cyn.” 8.1: c._dative_, φλόγες ἐ. ἄκροις τοῖς κέρασι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Fabius Maximus” 6; ὁ ἥλιος ἐπέλαμπε τῷ ἔργῳ [prev. author] “Arat.” 22, cf. Theo Sm. p.121H.: _metaphorically_, οὔριος.. ἐπίλαμψον ἐμῷ ἔρωτι, Κύπρι “AP” 5.16 (Gaet.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοῖς ἀπελπίζουσιν ἐ. <b>bring</b> them <b>new light</b>; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“OGI” 194.20 (Egypt, 1st c.BC), compare [prev. work]669.7 ([prev. passage], 1st c.AD). \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2>. <i>transitive</i>, <b>make to shine</b>, μόχθοι νεότατ᾽ ἐπέλαμψαν μυρίοι (so L.Dind. for μυρίοις) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Pi. “fragment” 172 (uncertain reading); τὸ ἀγαθὸν πᾶσιν ἐ. τοῖς νοητοῖς ἀλήθειαν 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 4.7.10 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>shine upon</b>, λόφῳ -ελάμπετο πήληξ 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 2.920. <br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3>. <b>illumine</b>, κολώνας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 164. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G7426","accentedUnicode":"ἐπιλάμπω","shortDef":"to shine forth","mediumDef":"to shine forth","stepGloss":"to shine forth